.TH PSNODED 1 "MAY 2013" Linux "PSNet Manual"
.SH NAME
psnoded \- PSNet router ("node") daemon
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B psnoded [options]
.SH DESCRIPTION
The PSNet router daemon maintains a list of connected clients and handles
forwarding broadcast messages to/from them.
.SH OPTIONS
.IP "-a, --directory-address <address>"
The address (either a domain name or an IP address) of a PSNet directory.
.IP "-l, --listen-port <port>"
The port to listen on for client requests.
.IP "-p, --directory-port <port>"
The port number that the PSNet directory is listening for requests on.
.IP "-t, --max-threads <threads>"
The maximum number of clients to service concurrently.
.SH FILES
.I /etc/psnetrc
.RS
Config file.  Any option that can be given on the command line can be given in
this file instead.  Option names are the same as the long version of the
corresponding command line option (e.g. "max-threads=1000").  Settings for
the router should be under the "Router" section in this file.
